sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Adversaries may abuse msiexec.exe to proxy execution of malicious payloads.
Msiexec.exe is the command-line utility for the Windows Installer and is thus commonly associated with executing installation packages (.msi)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potential Credential Dumping Attempt Using New NetworkProvider - REG
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects when an attacker tries to add a new network provider in order to dump clear text credentials, similar to how the NPPSpy tool does it

match_context.values: @{EventType=SetValue; EventID=13; Image=C:\Windows\System32\MsiExec.exe; Details=Windows File System Proxy; TargetObject=HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\WinFsp.Np\NetworkProvider\Name}
